summaries.short: (Series Premiere). Burned out and broke, former big-league pitcher Kenny Powers returns home to North Carolina to teach PE.
summaries.full: (Series Premiere). Burned out and broke, former big-league pitcher Kenny Powers returns home to North Carolina to teach PE at a local school he once attended. Wreaking havoc at school, around town and at the home of his brother Dustin, Kenny settles into his role as the town's loose-cannon agitator, setting his sights on winning back his high-school flame April.

summaries.short: Danny McBride stars in this outrageous comedy series about a former baseball star forced to work as a substitute schoolteacher.
summaries.full: Danny McBride stars in this outrageous comedy series about a former baseball star forced to work as a substitute schoolteacher.

summaries.short: To avoid selling his beloved jet ski, Kenny looks to score some extra cash as a spokesman for a car dealership.
summaries.full: To avoid selling his beloved jet ski, Kenny looks to score some extra cash by pitching himself as spokesman for a local luxury-car dealership. The gig threatens to turn into a fiasco when the dealership owner insists that Kenny pitch a fastball to a fan. Later Kenny and his driver, Clegg, make a memorable cameo appearance at the middle-school dance.

summaries.short: Kenny enlists the fawning Stevie to be his assistant; Dustin's wife Cassie offers to sell Kenny's memorabilia on eBay.
summaries.full: Kenny enlists the fawning Stevie to be his personal assistant, ordering him to scope out a high-school pitching phenom viewed as Kenny's big-league competition. Meanwhile, Dustin's wife Cassie offers to sell Kenny's baseball memorabilia on eBay, while Kenny gets serious about getting in shape by any means possible.
